descriptiveMetadata.title: al-Qurʼān
descriptiveMetadata.abstract: Illuminated Qurʾān from the library of Tippoo Ṣāḥib, presented to the University of Cambridge by the Court of Directors of the East India Company in 1806. The volume has two decorated medallions and two magnificent headpieces containing the Fātiḥa. The text of the Qurʾān is followed by some prayers, and a Fal-nāmah. The manuscript is not dated, but dates of ownership of 1028 A.H./1618 C.E. and 1066 A.H./1655 C.E. occur at the beginning
